@Brooklyn_Museum, thanks for having Ed take a look at the photos/comments!

Thanks for the corrections - I probably misinterpreted the map I was looking at for some of it.  When I was trying to discern what exhibits were visible in the photo, I found two maps which had slight differences in names, though, especially for the Washington Park (opposite view from this photo) end of the Midway.  I wonder if it has to do with maps drawn up based on plans of the fairgrounds, versus those made after the exhibits were in place?

@ChicagoGeek:  It's interesting to think about how many of our cities' quiet getaways were at one time bustling with people.
